{
  "texts": [
    "Humans generally engage in minimal exploration before making a choice.",
    "However, they search longer when they anticipate potential losses, requiring a more careful evaluation (Santos and Rosati, 2015).",
    "LLMs, like humans, may default to surface-level pattern matching when encountering adversarial queries.",
    "However, real-world adversarial queries are often subtle-written in ways that mimic safe queries through obfuscation, logical appeals, or expert endorsements.",
    "To ensure effective reasoning, fine-tuning must expose them to queries that necessitate deeper evaluation before response."
  ]
}